<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sacrifice1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sacrifice,</orth> subst. 1) the act of offering any thing to God: <bibl n="shak. wt 3.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.10.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 10, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.398" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 398</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 2, 5</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 12</bibl>. <cit><quote>give you thankful s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 9</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 167</bibl>.<lb />2) that which is offered or immolated: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.420" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 420</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.308" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 308</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 2, 3</bibl>.
<lb />3) that which is destroyed for the sake of something else: <cit><quote>the back is s. to the load,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>poor --s of our enmity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.304" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 304</bibl></cit>.

